    "safety_narrative": "Safety Manifesto: Given the patient's medical flags of a disc bulge at L4-L5 and a sensitive right knee when squatting deep, it is crucial to prioritize their safety and prevent further injury. The following movements and modifications are recommended to minimize the risk of exacerbating the existing conditions. Deep knee bends and lunges can put excessive stress on the knee joint, while heavy squats and deadlifts can exacerbate the lower back pain. Trunk rotation, whether loaded or unloaded, can also contribute to the strain on the lower back. To mitigate these risks, the patient should avoid deep knee bends and lunges, heavy squats and deadlifts, and limit trunk rotation. Additionally, using a lumbar roll for support and avoiding any movements that exacerbate lower back pain are essential precautions to take. By following these modifications and hard stops, the patient can safely work towards their goals of building muscle and increasing strength while focusing on longevity."
